Head yellow, with a brown stripe medially; short, semi-erect, gold vestiture; surface finely punctate; antenna not reaching base of posterior angles, same color as head, all antennomeres clothed with erect short hairs; antennomere 2 and antennomere 3 smaller than antennomere 4, antennomere 2 about 0.45 times as long as antennomere 4, antennomere 3 about 0.39 as long as antennomere 4; mandibles brown, with at least 3 long setae (
Fig. 9
).

Legs brown, vestiture black; tarsomeres 2–3 with heart-shaped lamellae, medially lighter than the rest of the tarsomere; tarsomere 4 about 0.5 times length tarsomere third (
Fig. 10
).
